(json 503 (title "Adaptive Algorithms Layer"))
(json 503 (status "completed"))
(json 503 (description "The updated milestone shifts the focus to researching Decentralized Identity (DID) methods and proposing an RFP for the integration of a DID hub. The goal is to explore multiple DID solutions while ensuring that identities are unique and cannot be duplicated. This milestone will ensure that users can use their preferred DID, including those already integrated into the SNET ecosystem, without compromising privacy or relying on third-party data storage."))
(json 503 (development_description "RFP outlining:
Research on applicable DID systems: Comprehensive research into various Decentralized Identity (DID) methods, including solutions such as Gitcoin Passport, Sentience Wallet, Solana ID, and WaLT from the SNET ecosystem.
Integration of DID systems: Exploration of how multiple DID solutions can be connected to a single hub without multiplying identities. This includes ensuring that a single person cannot present multiple identities in an event or voting process.
Concrete solution requirements: Defining a set of requirements for a solution that allows multiple DID systems to operate within a single framework while maintaining privacy and preventing identity duplication.
Self-owned identity management: Investigating how users can manage their own identification, such as using face recognition stored privately without relying on third-party KYC services, and ensuring that no face can appear twice across different systems."))
